content.text:
The database shows that there were indeed San Francisco community college sites (part of City College of San Francisco) that closed around 1989. Two closed on 1989-06-30: **Pacific Heights Adult High Sch** and **Mission Adult High**. Others closed later.

However, the database contains only school operational data (status, dates, enrollment, SAT scores, etc.). It has **no information about historic landmark designations**. There is no column or table that tracks whether a site was designated as a city historic landmark.
